  "local_port": 47432,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate or unlink your Roku device from your Roku account. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **On Your Roku Device:**\n   - Go to \"Settings\" from the home screen.\n   - Select \"System.\"\n   - Choose \"Advanced System Settings.\"\n   - Select \"Factory Reset\" or \"Factory Reset Everything.\" This will reset the device to its factory settings and unlink it from your Roku account.\n\n2. **On the Roku Website:**\n   - Log in to your account at the Roku website (my.roku.com).\n   - Go to \"My Account\" and scroll down to \"My linked devices.\"\n   - Find the device you want to unlink and click \"Remove\" or \"Deactivate.\"\n\nRemember, if you factory reset your device, it will erase all settings, preferences, and accounts associated with that device, and you'll need to set it up again if you decide to use it later.\n\nIf you are looking to deactivate your Roku account altogether, you would need to contact Roku support for further assistance.",
